Site conditions and comments [f:750]: outgoing tide

Beautiful day. Spoke with the fisherman in the pic. He's been coming to this site for the last 5 years from Staunton. I asked if he noticed any difference since the removal of the Jordan's Point dam. He said he noticed a big improvement--there were larger fish in this section. Last week he caught a 3 lb smallmouth bass.

I didn't have a pipette, so the 3 ml of H2O added to the solution was approximate. Also, I have a hard time determining e-coli colonies. It looks more pink than purple to me.
